30:47.240 --> 30:49.470
Cynthia, there's a whole cake
in this tin.

30:49.520 --> 30:53.150
I haven't seen that the entire
time I've been at Nonnatus.

30:53.200 --> 30:57.720
Sister Monica Joan's at Chummy's all
the time, looking after Lady Browne.

30:59.120 --> 31:01.830
We've got extra Horlicks
to go with it, too.

31:01.880 --> 31:05.350
When I went upstairs, all
the pupil midwives were asleep.

31:05.400 --> 31:06.880
Set 'em up, Joe!

31:13.240 --> 31:15.960
One commode. All ship-shape
and Bristol fashion.

31:17.320 --> 31:18.990
Right.

31:19.040 --> 31:21.520
I think it will serve well
over there.

31:25.160 --> 31:27.160
Perfect!

31:29.520 --> 31:31.630
Would you like me to find you
a change of clothes?

31:31.680 --> 31:34.550
You might feel more on top
of things in a pair of slacks.

31:34.600 --> 31:36.920
I think not! I'm a nurse, old bean.

31:38.240 --> 31:39.680
This is my armour.

31:56.920 --> 32:00.190
The Plaza Suite is
open for business!

32:00.240 --> 32:03.320
You take your time, Lady Browne.
There's no rush.

32:05.000 --> 32:08.000
Once I'm up...

32:09.560 --> 32:12.350
..I'm up, I suppose.

32:12.400 --> 32:14.550
You'll have no reason to come down.

32:14.600 --> 32:16.880
We've got it all laid on
for you up there.

32:18.400 --> 32:21.560
Come on. Stairway To The Stars time.

32:25.720 --> 32:29.630
The choir are absolutely
note perfect on Ave Verum Corpus.

32:29.680 --> 32:32.150
The perfect choice
for the competition.

32:32.200 --> 32:34.430
They could sing it
standing on their heads.

32:34.480 --> 32:36.230
Might make it a bit more
interesting.

32:36.280 --> 32:40.030
This one is just addressed to you,
but it looks official.

32:40.080 --> 32:41.600
Is it about the baby?

32:49.160 --> 32:52.110
No. It's from the festival.

32:52.160 --> 32:55.750
The East Ham Singers are doing
Ave Verum Corpus.

32:55.800 --> 32:58.710
No two choirs can sing the same
piece, and they entered first,

32:58.760 --> 33:00.830
so we have to find another song.

33:00.880 --> 33:02.310
Great(!)

33:02.360 --> 33:04.000
By Saturday!

33:06.160 --> 33:10.550
That's a lovely, steady heartbeat.
And Baby's head's well down.

33:10.600 --> 33:13.430
But I can't see any signs that
labour's under way just yet,

33:13.480 --> 33:16.070
especially now those twinges
have petered out.

33:16.120 --> 33:18.950
I know it sounds silly, but I
was kind of in the mood for it!

33:21.040 --> 33:22.790
Thank you.

33:22.840 --> 33:25.830
Hello, Mr Heckford!
You're back from Gibraltar!

33:25.880 --> 33:28.830
Ha-ha! Bless you, Nurse.
This is my cousin, Philip.

33:28.880 --> 33:30.150
Would you like a coffee?

33:30.200 --> 33:31.870
Yes, please.

33:31.920 --> 33:35.230
Last time Nurse Lee was here,
she was admiring your painting.

33:35.280 --> 33:37.030
Really?

33:37.080 --> 33:39.080
Yes. I was.

33:44.640 --> 33:47.880
And I win. Again.

33:51.360 --> 33:53.670
This is a much better game
than bridge.

33:53.720 --> 33:55.720
What did you say it was called?

33:57.600 --> 33:59.710
Strip Jack Naked, your ladyship.

33:59.760 --> 34:05.800
You know, I shouldn't object if you
called me by my Christian name.

34:07.080 --> 34:08.639
Artemis?

34:10.040 --> 34:18.040
Ghastly, isn't it? Sir Rex
used to call me Arthur, sometimes.

34:20.199 --> 34:23.120
I think it was on account
of my large feet.

34:24.679 --> 34:26.560
I passed them on to Camilla.

34:28.320 --> 34:30.230
Had you ever noticed?

34:30.280 --> 34:32.960
I love Camilla's feet.

34:34.800 --> 34:36.159
Good.

34:37.280 --> 34:41.909
I will not be defeated by this.
The choir have worked too hard.

34:41.960 --> 34:45.110
If I find the right song,
they can sing it simply.

34:45.159 --> 34:48.800
I won't need to rehearse them
too hard. Puff, please.

34:50.239 --> 34:52.710
You can always have one of your own.

34:52.760 --> 34:55.679
No, because that would make
me a smoker.

35:02.280 --> 35:07.630
♪ May the good Lord bless
and keep you... ♪

35:07.680 --> 35:09.830
Ah! Jim Reeves. Perfect!

35:09.880 --> 35:11.750
You and Jim Reeves.

35:11.800 --> 35:14.160
♪..When you are far away

35:15.320 --> 35:17.310
♪ May you find that... ♪

35:17.360 --> 35:21.510
This might just be a very
appropriate choice.

35:21.560 --> 35:24.760
♪..Day to day... ♪

35:26.000 --> 35:31.200
I feel like the princess
in The Princess And The Pea...

35:35.000 --> 35:39.950
..floating up on layer upon
layer of mattresses.

35:40.000 --> 35:42.350
It's probably the morphine.

35:42.400 --> 35:43.800
It's the pillows.

36:04.240 --> 36:10.280
I used to have a manicure once
a week in Rajputan.

36:12.680 --> 36:18.310
We had Nivea cream
sent over by diplomatic bag.

36:22.400 --> 36:27.240
I wouldn't mind a manicure today.

36:29.200 --> 36:33.200
You don't want to bother with all
that fuss and nonsense.

36:40.120 --> 36:43.560
Did I ever read you
The Princess And The Pea?

36:46.760 --> 36:48.120
I'm not sure you did.

36:52.600 --> 36:57.680
Perhaps I sent it to you
at boarding school.

37:00.160 --> 37:06.390
The post in India was abominable.

37:06.440 --> 37:14.440
So much got lost...on the way.

37:21.080 --> 37:22.710
Mind the wet stairs now, Sister.

37:22.760 --> 37:24.830
Don't want you tripping
over on them.

37:24.880 --> 37:28.640
Out of my way. I am in search of
the most particular accoutrements.

37:30.400 --> 37:36.550
Oh, Nurse Franklin, such unseemly
quantities of intimate apparel.

37:36.600 --> 37:38.510
Sister Monica Joan?

37:38.560 --> 37:42.270
Instead of skulking outside this
chamber, I suggest you enter,

37:42.320 --> 37:46.510
and offer me your aid.
Is this Nivea?

37:46.560 --> 37:49.470
I don't know but I reckon
that's for putting on your face.

37:49.520 --> 37:52.320
I need Nivea. And nail paint.

37:55.240 --> 37:57.120
Is that what you're looking for?

37:58.960 --> 38:02.870
You are very slow to see what
is before you.

38:02.920 --> 38:05.640
I think you should consult
an oculist.

38:06.680 --> 38:08.990
I'm sorry to press-gang you
when you must be so busy.

38:09.040 --> 38:11.670
But if we can't swell the numbers
of the choir, I don't think

38:11.720 --> 38:14.590
the judges will even entertain such
a simple piece of music.

38:14.640 --> 38:16.070
I think it's a terrific choice.

38:16.120 --> 38:18.670
There's no reason why it has to be
a piece of classical music.

38:18.720 --> 38:20.870
Quite. But we need more voices.

38:20.920 --> 38:24.190
I want children, adults,
the elderly, all involved,

38:24.240 --> 38:27.040
and singing side by side.
I like the sound of that.

38:29.080 --> 38:31.630
Hello! Back again, like a bad penny.

38:31.680 --> 38:35.270
Not at all.
Jeanette hoped it would be you.

38:39.560 --> 38:41.030
M blank...

38:41.080 --> 38:46.950
G, N, I, blank, blank, blank, E,
blank, blank, second word,

38:47.000 --> 38:51.880
blank B, S, E, blank, S,
blank, O, blank.

38:53.840 --> 38:55.560
Is it Magnificent Obsession?

38:57.960 --> 39:00.550
Excellent! Full marks.

39:00.600 --> 39:04.800
Philip! That was the last clue.
Now what are we going to do?

39:08.480 --> 39:11.710
You could eat some of this toast
I just made.

39:11.760 --> 39:13.880
Or maybe not.

39:18.320 --> 39:21.880
I can't. I simply can't.

39:23.560 --> 39:27.230
It's just too frivolous
when there is so much else to do.

39:27.280 --> 39:32.840
But there's almost nothing else
to do. And little time.

39:39.320 --> 39:40.800
I'm sorry, Sister...

39:42.640 --> 39:44.360
But I can't...

39:46.600 --> 39:48.400
I can't touch her.

39:50.560 --> 39:54.320
Unless it's a nursing matter,
but even then...

39:57.360 --> 39:58.920
I'm sorry. But it's true.

40:01.960 --> 40:04.920
My mother and I
did not have a tactile union.

40:06.440 --> 40:09.870
I did not regret it
when she was alive.

40:09.920 --> 40:11.280
But now...

40:12.600 --> 40:16.550
I think of Keats and how he cried...

40:16.600 --> 40:19.190
Touch has a memory!

40:19.240 --> 40:21.270
O say, love, say

40:21.320 --> 40:23.390
What can I do to kill it

40:23.440 --> 40:25.280
And be free?

41:41.840 --> 41:43.640
You've never done that before.

41:46.960 --> 41:48.120
Oh, I have...

41:50.960 --> 41:55.680
When you were very, very tiny.

42:11.240 --> 42:13.600
I've been going at it
all night, Nurse.

42:14.760 --> 42:17.030
This baby is never going to come.

42:17.080 --> 42:19.230
Jeanette.

42:19.280 --> 42:23.990
Your contractions are coming every
five minutes, steadily and surely.

42:24.040 --> 42:26.520
Baby's coming steadily
and surely, too.

42:27.600 --> 42:30.710
I don't want it to come
steadily and surely.

42:30.760 --> 42:32.760
I want it now. Sssh.

42:34.280 --> 42:35.640
Or soon.

42:38.760 --> 42:43.440
Let's set our hopes on "soon".
"Soon" seems very reasonable to me.

43:34.000 --> 43:35.640
The tide is turning.

43:37.840 --> 43:43.830
Time to lay aside your uniform.
Today, you are her child.

43:43.880 --> 43:48.080
I'm still a nurse.
I know what that sound means.

43:59.040 --> 44:03.270
That's it.
Good, now stay calm, Jeanette.

44:03.320 --> 44:06.070
This is a good, strong contraction.
It will help you,

44:06.120 --> 44:09.160
and it will help your baby
make its way into the world.

44:14.160 --> 44:17.310
I can't face another night of this.
Ssh. Come on.

44:17.360 --> 44:22.070
I can't. How long have I got?

44:22.120 --> 44:24.310
Sorry, it's impossible to say.

44:29.800 --> 44:31.240
Tell me what to do.

44:33.480 --> 44:36.870
Telephone Nonnatus House, tell them
I've had a lady with

44:36.920 --> 44:40.120
a very, very long first stage
and we need gas and air.

44:44.080 --> 44:46.000
And a new midwife.

45:14.080 --> 45:15.830
They're here.

45:15.880 --> 45:18.950
Oh, look at you two.
Poor little chicks.

45:19.000 --> 45:20.630
Are you the father? He's the cousin.

45:20.680 --> 45:22.470
Out.

45:22.520 --> 45:25.390
Right, case notes,
and then get your mac on.

45:25.440 --> 45:26.870
I'm not a betting woman,

45:26.920 --> 45:29.590
but I'll wager five bob you just
need a bit of blood sugar.

45:29.640 --> 45:32.350
I don't suppose you could
force down a Creamline toffee?

45:32.400 --> 45:35.710
No enema, I see. And you wonder why
things have stalled.

45:35.760 --> 45:38.190
I told Nurse Lee I didn't want one...

45:38.240 --> 45:41.110
Don't worry. You might just find
we've packed the wrong kit.

45:41.160 --> 45:44.560
Off you pop. Get a bit of shuteye.

45:46.440 --> 45:49.750
Will you let me
walk you back to the convent?

45:49.800 --> 45:52.910
I know my way.
I'd know it blindfolded.

45:52.960 --> 45:54.760
Nurse Lee, are you upset?

45:56.720 --> 45:58.120
Um...

46:01.680 --> 46:06.710
I've delivered so many babies
and I've never once not managed.

46:06.760 --> 46:11.590
Never once failed to do what
I was trained for.

46:11.640 --> 46:14.470
If it was just tiredness, I'd know
tomorrow would be better but...

46:14.520 --> 46:16.320
Please. Let me walk you back.

46:19.160 --> 46:24.320
Thank you but there's somewhere
I need to go first.

46:58.800 --> 47:00.160
Put this on.

47:02.960 --> 47:04.480
It's Mater's.

48:54.960 --> 48:56.520
I love you.

49:03.840 --> 49:07.560
'The departure of life
eclipses everything.

49:08.920 --> 49:13.110
'When a death is good,
the room is filled with peace,

49:13.160 --> 49:18.110
'and all the pain that
went before it is forgotten.

49:18.160 --> 49:21.750
'Where there was mystery,
there is knowledge,

49:21.800 --> 49:24.720
'where there was fear,
there is love.'

49:29.320 --> 49:31.670
May I have everybody's attention.

49:31.720 --> 49:35.710
As you know, Timothy has had to go
back for his sheet music,

49:35.760 --> 49:38.630
which he forgot.
As soon as he arrives,

49:38.680 --> 49:42.110
we will be catching the bus to
St Dacorum's church.

49:42.160 --> 49:45.150
The fare will be sixpence each
way but if anyone

49:45.200 --> 49:49.320
is in difficulties, will they please
talk to me or Mr Hereward.

49:50.520 --> 49:54.950
At last!
I wondered what had kept you.

49:55.000 --> 49:58.200
It was the adoption agency.
There was a phone call.

50:03.000 --> 50:04.920
Thank you, Doctor. You're welcome.

50:07.160 --> 50:10.430
Patrick. The adoption agency
have a baby girl.

50:10.480 --> 50:12.710
They need us to go straight there.

50:12.760 --> 50:14.550
Well, how much have they told you?

50:14.600 --> 50:17.670
Hardly anything! Just that
the mother is only 16.

50:17.720 --> 50:20.190
She was meant to be taking
the baby home with her,

50:20.240 --> 50:23.030
but at the last minute her parents
have changed their minds.

50:23.080 --> 50:26.750
That's terrible. Tim. That's why
they want a speedy settlement.

50:26.800 --> 50:29.720
To spare further
trauma for those involved.

50:34.360 --> 50:35.950
Mrs Turner shows great faith in us.

50:36.000 --> 50:38.870
I can't even get them in a straight
line! Oi, stop that.

50:38.920 --> 50:40.270
This is a community choir,

50:40.320 --> 50:42.390
not a conga line
at the Hammersmith Palais!

50:42.440 --> 50:44.710
And if you don't keep up,

50:44.760 --> 50:47.670
my next weapon will be
the heel of my stiletto!

50:47.720 --> 50:49.120
Charming(!) Go on!

50:51.000 --> 50:54.710
Baby Jones is at the far
end of the room, on the right.

50:54.760 --> 50:59.350
There's a little felt sunflower
attached to her cot.

50:59.400 --> 51:02.680
Perhaps Master Turner would like
to wait in the office with me?

51:11.400 --> 51:13.430
Do you want to go in alone?

51:13.480 --> 51:15.350
No, Patrick.

51:15.400 --> 51:18.950
This is the closest I'm ever going
to get to giving birth.

51:19.000 --> 51:21.720
And I want, and I need,
you to be by my side.

51:58.120 --> 51:59.600
What's she like?

52:01.760 --> 52:03.280
Close your eyes.

52:27.160 --> 52:28.880
Here's your mummy.

52:40.560 --> 52:42.080
We have a daughter.

