54:20.080 --> 54:23.710
♪ Till we meet

54:23.760 --> 54:31.400
♪ Till we meet again. ♪

54:32.600 --> 54:34.150
Goodbye! Congratulations!

54:34.200 --> 54:35.590
Good night.

54:35.640 --> 54:38.950
Shall I give the winner's trophy to
Mrs Turner, or would you like to?

54:39.000 --> 54:40.870
I don't think she'll even notice.

54:40.920 --> 54:43.550
She's been given
the prize of a lifetime today.

54:43.600 --> 54:45.390
The baby?

54:45.440 --> 54:47.750
It's just such a magical thought.

54:47.800 --> 54:52.080
These souls that have never met
being put together for a lifetime.

54:53.320 --> 54:56.270
That's quite a deep
thought for a Saturday evening.

54:56.320 --> 55:00.880
Well, it might surprise you to hear
this, but I'm quite a deep girl.

55:02.640 --> 55:03.920
I know.

55:16.640 --> 55:18.910
Why are we so low on
chloral hydrate?

55:18.960 --> 55:22.550
It's a sedative,
not a pre-labour cocktail snack.

55:22.600 --> 55:24.270
It should be administered sparingly!

55:24.320 --> 55:26.280
Sisters. And ladies...

55:27.840 --> 55:30.120
..Nurse Lee has some news for us.

55:34.080 --> 55:35.840
I've handed my notice in.

55:37.400 --> 55:39.000
Oh, I say!

55:40.360 --> 55:43.430
I'm moving away to take up
a position as a Staff Nurse

55:43.480 --> 55:46.470
at the Marie Curie Hospital.

55:46.520 --> 55:48.510
I want to work with the dying.

55:48.560 --> 55:51.240
And a cancer hospital
seems as good a place as any.

55:52.760 --> 55:54.910
Are you absolutely sure, Jenny?

55:54.960 --> 55:56.400
Yes.

55:58.000 --> 56:00.000
It's what I feel called to do.

56:06.120 --> 56:08.560
Right, Philip Worth, good luck.

56:09.920 --> 56:11.240
I...

56:13.360 --> 56:14.880
You look lovely.

56:16.680 --> 56:18.240
Go on.

56:22.920 --> 56:25.550
♪ I look at you... ♪

56:25.600 --> 56:28.270
Thank you. Lovely.

56:28.320 --> 56:31.670
♪..And I say to myself

56:31.720 --> 56:34.750
♪ What more could I want... ♪

56:34.800 --> 56:37.230
Come in. Thank you.

56:37.280 --> 56:40.390
♪..if I had you? ♪

56:40.440 --> 56:46.070
'I was leaving
midwifery behind but Nonnatus House

56:46.120 --> 56:51.590
'was where my family lived
and I would love it forever.

56:51.640 --> 56:57.430
'My time there had shaped me
as it shaped every life it touched.'

56:57.480 --> 57:02.590
♪..My head in a cloud... ♪

57:02.640 --> 57:10.230
The nightdress. You kept it?
For you. For better times to come.

57:10.280 --> 57:14.750
♪..I look at you
and I say to myself

57:14.800 --> 57:18.470
♪ What more could I want...? ♪

57:18.520 --> 57:22.070
'I would marry Philip
Worth, though I did not know

57:22.120 --> 57:25.710
'it then, and we would have two
daughters of our own.

57:25.760 --> 57:28.750
'The young can't see what lies ahead

57:28.800 --> 57:32.920
'and perhaps that is their blessing
and their sorrow.'

